<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-11T13:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-11T13:45:00-05:00" n="1238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1238">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/190</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-11T13:00:00-05:45">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>By vote of 29 to 8, House to-day at noon passed Nicaraguan Canal Treaty.
                            Both Houses ratified the Treaty and amendments exactly as passed by the
                            United States Senate.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>